    "author_channel_id": "UCOWr1KrtecAbgYI4dj7piGw",
    "text": "Were I to upsize this, I believe I would use 4 bellows, in a \"4 cylinder style\" opposed arrangement, with one of the drive cogs 90° out of phase with the other, to mitigate the lurching at the ends of the cycles, if this is possible (I can't see why not).\nBut yes, I can see some amusing possibilities here for air transfer. I am now thinking about a foot  or drill powered bellows for a forge or kiln.",
    "likes": 0,
