    "id": "UgxpB6fW8rCy1bAYmdl4AaABAg",
    "author": "@Teknik_Kality",
    "author_channel_id": "UCyF33GyNySZTgSPhZfoJzJA",
    "text": "One of the other benefits of this, is if you have mechanical rotation that is sensitive to changes in load, and a variable load, by attaching the load to the turbine, the varied load causes a variation in airflow losses over the turbine, while only minimally loading the original mechanical drive. You've created a slip transmission. There are obviously other more efficient methods, but it does work for that.",
    "likes": 0,
    "published_at": "2025-03-06T11:55:59Z",
    "reply_count": 1,
    "replies": [
      {
        "id": "UgxpB6fW8rCy1bAYmdl4AaABAg.AFKM68k5lYLAFKZHZbtaMG",
        "author": "@ThinkingandTinkering",
        "author_channel_id": "UC4AkVj-qnJxNtKuz3rkq16A",
        "text": "I like that mate - nice thinking and a great share - cheers",
        "likes": 0,
        "published_at": "2025-03-06T13:51:08Z"
      }
    ]
  },
