  {
    "id": "UgxxL30sTZatgn1pC1t4AaABAg",
    "author": "@Marian_Martin_Morgenstern",
    "author_channel_id": "UCxEMPng09G8OMGTE9JggMHA",
    "text": "If you have an intermittent source of energy, and no way of storing it electrically, storage as pressure in a vessel might be a way to go\nBellows are a way to produce pressure in high volumes over longer times\nAnd a simple Ballon can become a pressure regulator in a system like that... something like the bag of a bagpipe stores the breath of the player so the pipes don't stop playing while you breath in",
    "likes": 0,
    "published_at": "2025-03-06T09:50:58Z",
    "reply_count": 1,
    "replies": [
